author: Eric Yep
title: Oil Slips Ahead of U.S. Inventory Data
text: 0151 GMT [Dow Jones] Crude-oil futures edged lower in early Asian trade Wednesday ahead of key U.S. oil inventory and production data. Oil prices have been stuck in sideways trade this month amid continued oversupply and concerns about global growth. Late Tuesday, the American Petroleum Institute’s data showed weekly U.S. crude stockpiles rose by 4.6 million barrels. Official government data will be due later today; pricing agency Platts says it expects stockpiles to remain unchanged.
